  "raw_html": "<button type='button' role='link' class='btn btn-link p-0 text-start' id='link_0' aria-label=\" Pernod Ricard India Private Limited & Another versus Karanveer Singh Chhabra pdf\"  class='noToken' href='#' onclick=javascript:open_pdf('0','2025','2025_8_805_901','2025INSC981'); ><font size='4'> <strong>PERNOD RICARD INDIA PRIVATE LIMITED & ANOTHER<span class='fst-italic'> versus </span>KARANVEER SINGH CHHABRA </strong>- <span class='escrText'>[2025] 8 S.C.R. 805</span><span class='ncDisplay'>2025 INSC 981</span><input type='hidden' id='cnr' value=ESCR010006202025></button></font><br><strong>Coram : J.B. PARDIWALA<sup style=\"color: #268e97;font-size: 22px;top: 0;\" class=\"tooltip-sup\" data-tooltip=\"Author\">*</sup>, R MAHADEVAN</strong><br> Issue for Consideration Appellants, engaged in the manufacture and distribution of wines, liquors, and spirits, sell whisky under the brand names &lsquo;BLENDERS PRIDE&rsquo; and &lsquo;IMPERIAL BLUE&rsquo;, both of which are registered trademarks. The appellants also hold a registered trademark as the house mark of Appellant No.1, and is used both in India and internationally across various product lines. Respondent was marketing whisky under the mark &lsquo;LONDON PRIDE. The issue was whether the appellants were entitled to grant of interim injunction restraining the respondent<br><strong class='caseDetailsTD' ><span style='color:#212F3D' > Decision Date :</span><font color='green'> 14-08-2025</font><span style='color:#212F3D' > | Case No :</span><font color='green'> CIVIL APPEAL No. 10638/2025</font><span style='color:#212F3D' > | Disposal Nature :</span><font color='green'> Dismissed</font>   <span style='color:#212F3D' > |  Bench :</span><font color='green'> 2 Judges</font></strong><div class='row my-1 mt-2 border bg-light'><div class='col-auto'><a href='#' class='btn btn-outline-secondary btn-sm my-1' onclick=open_splitview('0','2025','2025_8_805_901','2025INSC981','S')><i <i class='fas fa-columns me-2'></i>